                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/11–3051: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Millard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-30T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 30, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>755. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 778, Nov 27. Note based on
                    reftel delivered today to Le Ghait, <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    official responsible for <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> matters. Urgency
                    of consultation emphasized. Le Ghait regretted necessity of withdrawal on
                    general principles.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 755, rptd info The Hague 44.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Millard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
